==English==

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[Old]] [[English]]'''

# The ancestor language of modern English, also called '''[[Anglo-Saxon]]''', spoken in Britain from about 400 AD to 1100 AD.  The language is a more inflected language, maintaining strong and weak verbs, nouns, and adjectives.  It has a clearly marked subjunctive mood, and has 5 cases of nouns and adjectives.

